\~above the city, on a tall column, stood the statue of the Happy Prince. He was gilded all over with thin leaves of fine gold, for eyes he had two bright sapphires, and a large red ruby glowed on his sword-hilt.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
He was very much admired indeed. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67He is as beautiful as a weathercock,\u8221\'81\'68 remarked one of the Town Councillors who wished to gain a reputation for having artistic tastes; \u8220\'81\'67only not quite so useful,\u8221\'81\'68 he added, fearing lest people should think him unpractical, which he really was not.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Why can\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66t you be like the Happy Prince?\u8221\'81\'68 asked a sensible mother of her little boy who was crying for the moon. \u8220\'81\'67The Happy Prince never dreams of crying for anything.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am glad there is some one in the world who is quite happy,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 muttered a disappointed man as he gazed at the wonderful statue.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
He looks just like an angel,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Charity Children as they came out of the cathedral in their bright scarlet cloaks and their clean white pinafores.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
How do you know?\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Mathematical Master, \u8220\'81\'67you have never seen one.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Ah! but we have, in our dreams,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 answered the children; and the Mathematical Master frowned and looked very severe, for he did not approve of children dreaming.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
One night there flew over the city a little Swallow. His friends had gone away to Egypt six weeks before, but he had stayed behind, for he was in love with the most beautiful Reed. He had met her early in the spring as he was flying down the river after a big yellow moth, and had been so attracted by her slender waist that he had stopped to talk to her.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Shall I love you?\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow, who liked to come to the point at once, and the Reed made him a low bow. So he flew round and round her, touching the water with his wings, and making silver ripples. This was his courtship, and it lasted all through the summer.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
It is a ridiculous attachment,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 twittered the other Swallows; \u8220\'81\'67she has no money, and far too many relations\u8221\'81\'68; and indeed the river was quite full of Reeds. Then, when the autumn came they all flew away.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
After they had gone he felt lonely, and began to tire of his lady-love. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67She has no conversation,\u8221\'81\'68 he said, \u8220\'81\'67and I am afraid that she is a coquette, for she is always flirting with the wind.\u8221\'81\'68 And certainly, whenever the wind blew, the Reed made the most graceful curtseys. \u8220\'81\'67I admit that she is domestic,\u8221\'81\'68 he continued, \u8220\'81\'67but I love travelling, and my wife, consequently, should love travelling also.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Will you come away with me?\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he said finally to her; but the Reed shook her head, she was so attached to her home.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
You have been trifling with me,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he cried. \u8220\'81\'67I am off to the Pyramids. Good-bye!\u8221\'81\'68 and he flew away.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
All day long he flew, and at night-time he arrived at the city. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67Where shall I put up?\u8221\'81\'68 he said; \u8220\'81\'67I hope the town has made preparations.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Then he saw the statue on the tall column.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I will put up there,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he cried; \u8220\'81\'67it is a fine position, with plenty of fresh air.\u8221\'81\'68 So he alighted just between the feet of the Happy Prince.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I have a golden bedroom,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he said softly to himself as he looked round, and he prepared to go to sleep; but just as he was putting his head under his wing a large drop of water fell on him. \u8220\'81\'67What a curious thing!\u8221\'81\'68 he cried; \u8220\'81\'67there is not a single cloud in the sky, the stars are quite clear and bright, and yet it is raining. The climate in the north of Europe is really dreadful. The Reed used to like the rain, but that was merely her selfishness.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Then another drop fell.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
What is the use of a statue if it cannot keep the rain off?\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he said; \u8220\'81\'67I must look for a good chimney-pot,\u8221\'81\'68 and he determined to fly away.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
But before he had opened his wings, a third drop fell, and he looked up, and saw\uc2 \u8212\'81\'5cAh! what did he see?\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
The eyes of the Happy Prince were filled with tears, and tears were running down his golden cheeks. His face was so beautiful in the moonlight that the little Swallow was filled with pity.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Who are you?\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he said.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am the Happy Prince.\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Why are you weeping then?\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 asked the Swallow; \u8220\'81\'67you have quite drenched me.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
When I was alive and had a human heart,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 answered the statue, \u8220\'81\'67I did not know what tears were, for I lived in the Palace of Sans-Souci, where sorrow is not allowed to enter. In the daytime I played with my companions in the garden, and in the evening I led the dance in the Great Hall. Round the garden ran a very lofty wall, but I never cared to ask what lay beyond it, everything about me was so beautiful. My courtiers called me the Happy Prince, and happy indeed I was, if pleasure be happiness. So I lived, and so I died. And now that I am dead they have set me up here so high that I can see all the ugliness and all the misery of my city, and though my heart is made of lead yet I cannot chose but weep.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
What! is he not solid gold?\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow to himself. He was too polite to make any personal remarks out loud.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Far away,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 continued the statue in a low musical voice, \u8220\'81\'67far away in a little street there is a poor house. One of the windows is open, and through it I can see a woman seated at a table. Her face is thin and worn, and she has coarse, red hands, all pricked by the needle, for she is a seamstress. She is embroidering passion-flowers on a satin gown for the loveliest of the Queen\u8217\'81\'66s maids-of-honour to wear at the next Court-ball. In a bed in the corner of the room her little boy is lying ill. He has a fever, and is asking for oranges. His mother has nothing to give him but river water, so he is crying. Swallow, Swallow, little Swallow, will you not bring her the ruby out of my sword-hilt? My feet are fastened to this pedestal and I cannot move.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am waited for in Egypt,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow. \u8220\'81\'67My friends are flying up and down the Nile, and talking to the large lotus-flowers. Soon they will go to sleep in the tomb of the great King. The King is there himself in his painted coffin. He is wrapped in yellow linen, and embalmed with spices. Round his neck is a chain of pale green jade, and his hands are like withered leaves.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Swallow, Swallow, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67will you not stay with me for one night, and be my messenger? The boy is so thirsty, and the mother so sad.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I don\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66t think I like boys,\u8221\'81\'68 answered the Swallow. \u8220\'81\'67Last summer, when I was staying on the river, there were two rude boys, the miller\u8217\'81\'66s sons, who were always throwing stones at me. They never hit me, of course; we swallows fly far too well for that, and besides, I come of a family famous for its agility; but still, it was a mark of disrespect.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
But the Happy Prince looked so sad that the little Swallow was sorry. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67It is very cold here,\u8221\'81\'68 he said; \u8220\'81\'67but I will stay with you for one night, and be your messenger.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Thank you, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
So the Swallow picked out the great ruby from the Prince\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s sword, and flew away with it in his beak over the roofs of the town.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
He passed by the cathedral tower, where the white marble angels were sculptured. He passed by the palace and heard the sound of dancing. A beautiful girl came out on the balcony with her lover. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67How wonderful the stars are,\u8221\'81\'68 he said to her, \u8220\'81\'67and how wonderful is the power of love!\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I hope my dress will be ready in time for the State-ball,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 she answered; \u8220\'81\'67I have ordered passion-flowers to be embroidered on it; but the seamstresses are so lazy.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
He passed over the river, and saw the lanterns hanging to the masts of the ships. He passed over the Ghetto, and saw the old Jews bargaining with each other, and weighing out money in copper scales. At last he came to the poor house and looked in. The boy was tossing feverishly on his bed, and the mother had fallen asleep, she was so tired. In he hopped, and laid the great ruby on the table beside the woman\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s thimble. Then he flew gently round the bed, fanning the boy\u8217\'81\'66s forehead with his wings. \u8220\'81\'67How cool I feel,\u8221\'81\'68 said the boy, \u8220\'81\'67I must be getting better\u8221\'81\'68; and he sank into a delicious slumber.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Then the Swallow flew back to the Happy Prince, and told him what he had done. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67It is curious,\u8221\'81\'68 he remarked, \u8220\'81\'67but I feel quite warm now, although it is so cold.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
That is because you have done a good action,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince. And the little Swallow began to think, and then he fell asleep. Thinking always made him sleepy.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
When day broke he flew down to the river and had a bath. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67What a remarkable phenomenon,\u8221\'81\'68 said the Professor of Ornithology as he was passing over the bridge. \u8220\'81\'67A swallow in winter!\u8221\'81\'68 And he wrote a long letter about it to the local newspaper. Every one quoted it, it was full of so many words that they could not understand.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
To-night I go to Egypt,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow, and he was in high spirits at the prospect. He visited all the public monuments, and sat a long time on top of the church steeple. Wherever he went the Sparrows chirruped, and said to each other, \u8220\'81\'67What a distinguished stranger!\u8221\'81\'68 so he enjoyed himself very much.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
When the moon rose he flew back to the Happy Prince. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67Have you any commissions for Egypt?\u8221\'81\'68 he cried; \u8220\'81\'67I am just starting.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Swallow, Swallow, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67will you not stay with me one night longer?\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am waited for in Egypt,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 answered the Swallow. \u8220\'81\'67To-morrow my friends will fly up to the Second Cataract. The river-horse couches there among the bulrushes, and on a great granite throne sits the God Memnon. All night long he watches the stars, and when the morning star shines he utters one cry of joy, and then he is silent. At noon the yellow lions come down to the water\u8217\'81\'66s edge to drink. They have eyes like green beryls, and their roar is louder than the roar of the cataract.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Swallow, Swallow, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67far away across the city I see a young man in a garret. He is leaning over a desk covered with papers, and in a tumbler by his side there is a bunch of withered violets. His hair is brown and crisp, and his lips are red as a pomegranate, and he has large and dreamy eyes. He is trying to finish a play for the Director of the Theatre, but he is too cold to write any more. There is no fire in the grate, and hunger has made him faint.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I will wait with you one night longer,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow, who really had a good heart. \u8220\'81\'67Shall I take him another ruby?\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Alas! I have no ruby now,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince; \u8220\'81\'67my eyes are all that I have left. They are made of rare sapphires, which were brought out of India a thousand years ago. Pluck out one of them and take it to him. He will sell it to the jeweller, and buy food and firewood, and finish his play.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Dear Prince,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow, \u8220\'81\'67I cannot do that\u8221\'81\'68; and he began to weep.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Swallow, Swallow, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67do as I command you.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
So the Swallow plucked out the Prince\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s eye, and flew away to the student\u8217\'81\'66s garret. It was easy enough to get in, as there was a hole in the roof. Through this he darted, and came into the room. The young man had his head buried in his hands, so he did not hear the flutter of the bird\u8217\'81\'66s wings, and when he looked up he found the beautiful sapphire lying on the withered violets.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am beginning to be appreciated,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he cried; \u8220\'81\'67this is from some great admirer. Now I can finish my play,\u8221\'81\'68 and he looked quite happy.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
The next day the Swallow flew down to the harbour. He sat on the mast of a large vessel and watched the sailors hauling big chests out of the hold with ropes. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67Heave a-hoy!\u8221\'81\'68 they shouted as each chest came up. \u8220\'81\'67I am going to Egypt\u8221\'81\'68! cried the Swallow, but nobody minded, and when the moon rose he flew back to the Happy Prince.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am come to bid you good-bye,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 he cried.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Swallow, Swallow, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67will you not stay with me one night longer?\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
It is winter,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 answered the Swallow, \u8220\'81\'67and the chill snow will soon be here. In Egypt the sun is warm on the green palm-trees, and the crocodiles lie in the mud and look lazily about them. My companions are building a nest in the Temple of Baalbec, and the pink and white doves are watching them, and cooing to each other. Dear Prince, I must leave you, but I will never forget you, and next spring I will bring you back two beautiful jewels in place of those you have given away. The ruby shall be redder than a red rose, and the sapphire shall be as blue as the great sea.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
In the square below,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Happy Prince, \u8220\'81\'67there stands a little match-girl. She has let her matches fall in the gutter, and they are all spoiled. Her father will beat her if she does not bring home some money, and she is crying. She has no shoes or stockings, and her little head is bare. Pluck out my other eye, and give it to her, and her father will not beat her.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I will stay with you one night longer,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow, \u8220\'81\'67but I cannot pluck out your eye. You would be quite blind then.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Swallow, Swallow, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67do as I command you.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
So he plucked out the Prince\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s other eye, and darted down with it. He swooped past the match-girl, and slipped the jewel into the palm of her hand. \u8220\'81\'67What a lovely bit of glass,\u8221\'81\'68 cried the little girl; and she ran home, laughing.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Then the Swallow came back to the Prince. \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67You are blind now,\u8221\'81\'68 he said, \u8220\'81\'67so I will stay with you always.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
No, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the poor Prince, \u8220\'81\'67you must go away to Egypt.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I will stay with you always,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow, and he slept at the Prince\u8217\'81\'66s feet.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
All the next day he sat on the Prince\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s shoulder, and told him stories of what he had seen in strange lands. He told him of the red ibises, who stand in long rows on the banks of the Nile, and catch gold-fish in their beaks; of the Sphinx, who is as old as the world itself, and lives in the desert, and knows everything; of the merchants, who walk slowly by the side of their camels, and carry amber beads in their hands; of the King of the Mountains of the Moon, who is as black as ebony, and worships a large crystal; of the great green snake that sleeps in a palm-tree, and has twenty priests to feed it with honey-cakes; and of the pygmies who sail over a big lake on large flat leaves, and are always at war with the butterflies.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Dear little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67you tell me of marvellous things, but more marvellous than anything is the suffering of men and of women. There is no Mystery so great as Misery. Fly over my city, little Swallow, and tell me what you see there.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
So the Swallow flew over the great city, and saw the rich making merry in their beautiful houses, while the beggars were sitting at the gates. He flew into dark lanes, and saw the white faces of starving children looking out listlessly at the black streets. Under the archway of a bridge two little boys were lying in one another\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s arms to try and keep themselves warm. \u8220\'81\'67How hungry we are!\u8221\'81\'68 they said. \u8220\'81\'67You must not lie here,\u8221\'81\'68 shouted the Watchman, and they wandered out into the rain.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Then he flew back and told the Prince what he had seen.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am covered with fine gold,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67you must take it off, leaf by leaf, and give it to my poor; the living always think that gold can make them happy.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Leaf after leaf of the fine gold the Swallow picked off, till the Happy Prince looked quite dull and grey. Leaf after leaf of the fine gold he brought to the poor, and the children\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s faces grew rosier, and they laughed and played games in the street. \u8220\'81\'67We have bread now!\u8221\'81\'68 they cried.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Then the snow came, and after the snow came the frost. The streets looked as if they were made of silver, they were so bright and glistening; long icicles like crystal daggers hung down from the eaves of the houses, everybody went about in furs, and the little boys wore scarlet caps and skated on the ice.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
The poor little Swallow grew colder and colder, but he would not leave the Prince, he loved him too well. He picked up crumbs outside the baker\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s door when the baker was not looking and tried to keep himself warm by flapping his wings.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
But at last he knew that he was going to die. He had just strength to fly up to the Prince\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s shoulder once more. \u8220\'81\'67Good-bye, dear Prince!\u8221\'81\'68 he murmured, \u8220\'81\'67will you let me kiss your hand?\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
I am glad that you are going to Egypt at last, little Swallow,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Prince, \u8220\'81\'67you have stayed too long here; but you must kiss me on the lips, for I love you.\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
It is not to Egypt that I am going,\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 said the Swallow. \u8220\'81\'67I am going to the House of Death. Death is the brother of Sleep, is he not?\u8221\'81\'68\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
And he kissed the Happy Prince on the lips, and fell down dead at his feet.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
At that moment a curious crack sounded inside the statue, as if something had broken. The fact is that the leaden heart had snapped right in two. It certainly was a dreadfully hard frost.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
Early the next morning the Mayor was walking in the square below in company with the Town Councillors. As they passed the column he looked up at the statue: \uc2 \u8220\'81\'67Dear me! how shabby the Happy Prince looks!\u8221\'81\'68 he said.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
\uc2 \u8220\'81\'67\uc1 }{\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0\i0\b0\f4\loch
How shabby indeed!\uc2 \u8221\'81\'68 cried the Town Councillors, who always agreed with the Mayor; and they went up to look at it.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s17\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl288\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf18\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\qj\widctlpar{\rtlch\afs20 \ltrch\loch\scaps0\caps0\cf1\fs20\expnd0\expndtw0
